The read command, r, is used to read audio data from a file, or from
another edit session.  Type r, a space, a filename, and press enter,
to read from a file.  Wildcard characters are supported. Each matching
file is placed in its own edit session.  Filename completion is supported
by pressing the tab character.  To read from another edit session, tell
the r command where to insert the data by typing a block address first,
then the r, and without a space, the number of the session to be read.
The sample rate and number of channels of the new data will be converted
to match those of the current session.  A file is said to be "readable"
if it can be accessed by the libsndfile library, or if it has one of
the supported filename suffixes.

